	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=80045><span id=Scholar>Tenser</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>16 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Here's what I've learned about leveling an Erudite Paladin. I know they are rare, but why not be different? There are surely other ways to do this, but this was the way I found to be best. This recipe could be exactly followed by a human or half-elf paladin out of Qeynos.<br><br>Level 1-4: Don't waste your time with Toxxulia Forest. I've seen Heretics within visible distance of the patio that would toast a newbie paladin. If anything, hunt there until you got a few silver to buy sharpening stones.&nbsp;&nbsp;Get on the boat, don't think twice, just grab it. Follow Prexus' ways and get on the water. Go to Qeynos. Get a bind at the front gate and do the Qeynos newbie area. A million times safer with many, many more critters to kill, and more players around that can help you when you're in trouble, or higher level folks that will buff you out of kindness. The only danger here is Fippy or Queen Klicknik, but the first announces himself and you might start killing him at 4th level, and the Queen is a pretty rare spawn.<br><br>Level 5-6/7: Qeynos Hills. With a long zone line, you can stay near it and kill bats, wolves, gnoll scouts, and perhaps a bear or two. If you get in trouble, you can zone out or run for one of the guards that walks along the trail. If you stay within guard or zone reach, this is extremely safe. The only danger is Holly Whatsername, but when you see her just kill bats instead of wolves or bears; and Tomar Vax (or whatsisname), but he doesn't head to the zone, he mostly stays by the hills or on the plains north of the road marker.<br><br>Level 7/8-10: Blackburrow. At this level, you can stay up top or just down at the bleachers/bridge area and do well. Watch out for trains, of course. Those are the only reason you should die, your or someone else's bad pulls and adds. Start up top and work your way down. Get a group of three to five and camp the elite ledge, or one of the other relatively safe areas. Collect every single NO DROP gnoll tooth you find and turn them in to Captain Tillin at the Warrior's Guild in South Qeynos. You'll be amazed and delighted by the experience you get from a stack of them. They aren't like the Crushbone belts and pads, but you'll collect them much faster. <br><br>If Blackburrow is crowded or you have idiots training you ever five minutes, head to West Karana. Watch out for the rare werewolf or wandering hill giant, and go to one of the two guard towers along the path. You can pull giant spiders, wolves, bears, and so on and be within running distance of guards if you are in trouble. Only problem here, other than the two big dangers mentioned above, is that action is slow. Very much the opposite of Blackburrow.<br><br>11-14 Erud's Crossing: Absolutely go here. I don't understand why someone does the dangerous inner world of Blackburrow when you can go here and make good experience and, for the level, incredible loot. Hunt wisps only. Wisps wisps wisps. Having a partner or two is nice, but not too many or you'll never fill that backback with Greater Lightstones. Other than the occasional zombie sailor, island madman, or fire elemental, and of course, swarming wisps, this is a great place to go. If you solo, be prepared to die now and then. No guards to run to, so if three wisps jump you, plan on using the /loc command for corpse retrieval. I recommend setting up near a shoreline, preferable over by the ogre so at night you don't get a zombie sailor or two slap you upside the back of the head. Use some arrows to pull to the shoreline to decrease the chances of adds, even if the arrows do no damage. Make sure you have a magic weapon by now; advertise in Qeynos, someone probably has an old unused  magic weapon they'll sell you cheaply. There is a Kerran merchant at Erud's Crossing that will sell you food and water and buy those plain old lightstones for a little under one plat, so other than needing to bank or buy arrows, you really need never leave here. Take those Greater Lightstones to North Karana (carefully, along the shoreline and WK/NK zone line if needed) and trade them to the gypsy that has the Concordance of Research quest. You get a small amount of XP for each, and you can sell it back to her for 8-9 plat, depending on faction and charisma. Do that, and get the heck out of North Karana. Now, for your level, you'll have some serious cash for buying armor and weaponry.<br><br>14-17: I find this to be a tough set of levels. You'll get too high to get decent XP in Blackburrow or Erud's Crossing. The inner areas of the Warrens are, it seems to me, usually devoid of groups for this level. Mobs in Western Karana are mostly too low for XP other than the occasional Grizzly or Brigand. The bandits are fine at the lower end, but XP fades as you gain levels. <br><br>The best possibilities, IMO are to travel a bit. Highhold Pass might be a bit tough for you still, so I recommend heading to Everfrost. Yes, with all those barbarians you'll be a raisin in a bowl of oatmeal (i.e. Oho boyo are you going to stick out), but get in a group to hunt on the plain not far from Bandl. Hunting wandering orcs, snow leopards, and mammoth calves will be good XP, with Bandl nearby you'll have some safety, and all those shamen, warriors, and rogues should be happy to have someone that can do a little healing and tank for them. You can sell mammoth skins for a plat each, and save that mammoth meat for a future baking friend, they'll thank you.<br><br>Anyone else with good ideas for these levels?<br><br>After 17, the choices are just too many. Now you have money and can get a gate from a druid/wizard instead of running through Kithicor. You could go to Oasis, Unrest, Highhold Pass, South Karana, to name a few, or around 19 or so (depends on opinion) you can try Lake of Ill Omen. From here on, you're in the same boat as everyone else.<br><br>Just my opinion, differing thoughts presented intelligently are welcomed.<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Tenser - Mighty Enchanter<br>Hasan - The Erudite Paladin</td></td></tr>
